Re: Japanese sentences in the Informal Present Progressive
by Hyperworm » Sat 08.29.2009 4:46 pm Mr.Paper wrote:nihongo o benkyoushiteiru (ga achieves nothing here besides making "nihongo" the subject, incorrectly)inu to hashitteiru(to and o don't go together; just use to on its own.)The rest are fine, unless I missed something ^^
